{
  "texts": [
    "However, while harnessing the power of AI, ethical considerations must also be considered.",
    "The use of AI in education involves handling sensitive student data, which may cause harm to students if misused.",
    "Educators and researchers must ensure that all data-driven insights are derived and utilized responsibly.",
    "This means being transparent about data collection and usage policies, implementing robust data privacy and security measures, and regularly reviewing and updating these measures in line with evolving ethical standards and regulations (Gimpel et al., 2018).",
    "Illustrative Example: Automated Writing EvaluationAutomated writing evaluation (AWE) has evolved significantly since its initial discussion in scholarly literature by Warschauer and Ware in 2006, who set a foundational research agenda for its development."
  ]
}